com.polarion.alm.ui.client

Class PublicJS

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.polarion.alm.ui.client.PublicJS

  • public final class PublicJS
extends java.lang.Object
    This class lists all public JavaScript functions which can be used in Live Report pages, Plans, Test Runs, Documents and Classic Wiki pages. See individual functions for examples of usage.
    Since:
    3.9.2

    • Method Detail

      • navigateFromFrame

        public static void navigateFromFrame(@Nullable
                                     java.lang.String urlHash)
        Navigates main Polarion portal area to different part of Polarion or invokes special action.

        The only supported navigation target is #action:create:Project which opens "Create New Project" dialog.

        Example of usage in Live Report page: 

         <button onclick="javascript:top.navigateFromFrame('#action:create:Project');">Create Project</button>
        Parameters:
        urlHash - navigation target

      • createDocument

        public static void createDocument(@NotNull
                                  java.lang.String spaceId,
                                  @NotNull
                                  java.lang.String projectId)
        Opens "Create New Document" dialog in given project and space.

        Example of usage in Live Report page: 

         <button onclick="javascript:top.createDocument('$page.reference.spaceReference.spacePath', '$page.reference.projectId');">Create New Document</button>
        Parameters:
        spaceId - space id (not null)
        projectId - project id (not null)

      • duplicateDocument

        public static void duplicateDocument(@NotNull
                                     java.lang.String name,
                                     @NotNull
                                     java.lang.String spaceId,
                                     @NotNull
                                     java.lang.String projectId)
        Opens "Reuse Document" dialog for given document.

        Example of usage in Live Report page: 

         <button onclick="javascript:top.duplicateDocument('MasterDocument', '$page.reference.spaceReference.spacePath', '$page.reference.projectId');">Reuse Document</button>
        Parameters:
        name - document name (not null)
        spaceId - space id (not null)
        projectId - project id (not null)

      • createChildPlan

        public static void createChildPlan(@NotNull
                                   java.lang.String projectId,
                                   @Nullable
                                   java.lang.String parentPath,
                                   @Nullable
                                   java.lang.String templatePath,
                                   @Nullable
                                   java.lang.String templateLabel)
        Opens "Create New Plan" dialog in given project.

        Example of usage in Live Report page: 

         <button onclick="javascript:top.createChildPlan('$page.reference.projectId', null, '${page.reference.projectId}/release', 'Release');">Create Release Plan</button>
        Parameters:
        projectId - project id (not null)
        parentPath - path to parent Plan to be preselected or null to not preselect anything
        templatePath - path to Plan template or null to allow user to select
        templateLabel - label to use in dialog name "Create New LABEL" or null for default "Plan"

      • createTestRun

        public static void createTestRun(@NotNull
                                 java.lang.String projectId,
                                 @Nullable
                                 java.lang.String templateId,
                                 @Nullable
                                 java.lang.String id)
        Opens "Create Test Run" dialog in given project with given Test Run id filled and given Test Run template selected.

        If "Generated Test Run IDs" are enabled and Test Run template is given then new Test Run will be created immediately.

        Example of usage in Test Run template: 

         <button onclick="javascript:top.createTestRun('$testRun.projectId', '$testRun.id', null);">Create Test Run</button>
        Parameters:
        projectId - project id (not null)
        templateId - Test Run template id or null to allow user to select
        id - new Test Run id or null (is ignored if "Generated Test Run IDs" are enabled)

      • createTestRunWithTitle

        public static void createTestRunWithTitle(@NotNull
                                          java.lang.String projectId,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String templateId,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String id,
                                          @Nullable
                                          java.lang.String title)
        Opens "Create Test Run" dialog in given project with given Test Run id and title filled and given Test Run template selected.

        If "Generated Test Run IDs" are enabled and Test Run template is given then new Test Run will be created immediately.

        Template title is used when title is null.

        Example of usage in Test Run template: 

         <button onclick="javascript:top.createTestRunWithTitle('$testRun.projectId', '$testRun.id', null, null);">Create Test Run</button>
        Parameters:
        projectId - project id (not null)
        templateId - Test Run template id or null to allow user to select
        id - new Test Run id or null (is ignored if "Generated Test Run IDs" are enabled)
        title - new Test Run title or null

      • executeWidgetAction

        public static void executeWidgetAction(@NotNull
                                       com.google.gwt.dom.client.Node referenceNode,
                                       boolean showPopupProgressIndicator,
                                       @Nullable
                                       java.lang.String actionId)
        Can be used by JavaScript in RichPageWidget on client to execute RichPageWidget.executeAction(RichPageWidgetActionContext) on server.
        Parameters:
        referenceNode - - used to identify to which widget this action belongs. Can be any node inside the widget or the main widget element (the one with data-widget attribute).

        If the node is element and contains any of the attributes mentioned in javadoc of RichPageWidget.executeAction(RichPageWidgetActionContext) then these attributes are processed in same way as described in javadoc for executeAction method, even the data-action-id attribute.

        showPopupProgressIndicator - - whether the popup progress indicator should be shown

        actionId - - optional id of the action which will be accessible using RichPageWidgetActionContext.actionId(). Overrides the value of the data-action-id attribute if it is not empty string.
        Since:
        3.9.2
